Stylizing with AI: Woodcut style examples using Stable Diffusion! Dreambooth can be trained on anything - not just a person's face (as Lensa does). Here are a series of example where I did a dreambooth fine-tune using an old dataset I have of scans from an Aesop’s Fables woodcut illustrations book published by the Met Museum. (Last couple images are from the book)

A lot of the process is comparing denoise amount (how close it hews to the init image) and CFG Scale (how close it matches the prompt) alongside different seeds. There are so many controls; it's extremely powerful! 

Images include some variations along with process grids.  

We've come a long way since neural style transfer!

_________________________

Smoke and mirrored reflection of reality. Collaboration with @nathan_shipley_vfx and @hok 

Using some simple iPhone videos of Hok’s choreography with dancer @erica_klein , the footage was given a slit scan a long exposure effect. The clip was then processed with @runwayapp #gen1 to create an insane smoke simulation— something that would have normally taken a week to develop. Finally it was ran through stable diffusion img2img to add in more realistic smoke details. 

A study in how how far the human form can be abstracted and our mind still searches people.
 
#smoke #dance #ai #animation

Testing DALL-E 3 by asking for my usual test prompt: a picture of clouds that look like puppies. BUT then building a whole universe! This is a cutdown of a 30 minute session where I played with the ChatGPT-powered DALL-E 3 and ended up going much further than the usual dog clouds.

“Pretend that Sky Dachshund is like a magic carpet ride company for dogs.  We’ve seen their logo and what their shirts look like, but let’s make a poster of what it looks like when dogs get to go on a Sky Dachshund ride! Instead of a magic carpet, though, it’s a flying doggie bed.”

#dalle3

DALL-E 3 Test:

Someone on Reddit suggested I ask DALL-E 3 to create a list of 50 objects and then generate an image of them.  It did.

Then I asked asked it "Can you create an image of a surfer holding these objects in a big overwhelming pile as he struggles to surf?" 

Images to the right show process and a variation with a lower angle and an “elderly Spanish woman” because why not. 

#Dalle3 #aiart #openai

AI VFX: In-painting on moving video!

6 tests combining a prompt, footage, and a mask to create VFX shots. Made with @paultrillo 
 
This feels like the start of an entirely new paradigm in VFX. Shots like these could take days using traditional techniques but render in minutes here.

Mime footage is the talented Derek Loughran!

As with my previous post, these are created in ComfyUI using:

- AnimateDiff-Evolved Nodes
- IPAdapter Plus for some shots
- Advanced ControlNet to apply in-painting controlnet
- KJNodes from are helpful for mask operations (grow/shrink)

Animated masks created in After Effects!

______________________
